{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17412788","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17412788"},"attributes":{"position":17,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T07:39:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T07:39:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"333"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487376"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:08:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:08:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"333"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261074"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:50+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:40:20+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":19,"questionsAnswered":7,"marksTotal":19,"marksAttainable":7,"marksAttempted":7,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T07:39:59+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.14,"questionsCorrect":1,"marksCorrect":1},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/333"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.06,0.33,0.56,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"333"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41638"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/333"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"333"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26556"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"339"},{"type":"tags","id":"1155"},{"type":"tags","id":"5789"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"114"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17301"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37252"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41638","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/41638"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 85-year-old nursing home resident is assessed after complaining of increasing pain in the left side of her face. These symptoms have been worsening over the last two days. She has never experienced similar symptoms before. She requires help with her meals and has poor oral hygiene due to her dementia. On examination there is a 5 cm firm, tender swelling anterior to her left ear with associated skin erythema. Gentle pressure on the swelling produces pus at the opening to the left parotid duct.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Regular use of a sialagogue","Antiseptic mouth washes","Antibiotics","Incision and drainage","Parotidectomy"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has acute suppurative (bacterial) parotitis, characterised by a firm and tender mass, which may extend from the ear to as far as the angle of the mandible, with associated purulent expression from the ipsilateral parotid duct. Most patients are afebrile. This is a well recognised complication of poor oral hygiene. The typical patient is either a nursing home resident or someone just recovering from a major illness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInitial treatment consists of intravenous \u003Cstrong\u003Eantibiotics\u003C/strong\u003E and rehydration. The most common causative organisms are \u003Cem\u003ES. aureus\u003C/em\u003E, \u003Cem\u003EH\u003C/em\u003E. \u003Cem\u003Einfluenzae\u003C/em\u003E, and oral anaerobes. \u003Cstrong\u003EAntiseptic mouth wash\u003C/strong\u003E is ineffective at treating suppurative parotitis as it has poor penetrance into the parotid gland. \u003Cstrong\u003ESialagogues\u003C/strong\u003E may provide some symptomatic relief, however are not the definitive treatment in this condition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncision and drainage \u003C/strong\u003Emay be considered in parotitis refractory to antibiotics, or in the presence of complications such as fistula formation. However, it is not an appropriate initial treatment in this patient. \u003Cstrong\u003EParotidectomy\u003C/strong\u003E may be considered in patients with recurrent suppurative parotitis, usually due to an underlying comorbidity, however it is not indicated in an initial episode.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["When it occurs, acute parotitis is most often associated with poor oral hygiene."],"references":["Brook I. Acute bacterial suppurative parotitis: microbiology and management. J Craniofac Surg. 2003 Jan;14(1):37-40. doi: 10.1097/00001665-200301000-00006. PMID: 12544218."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26556"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"333"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"26556","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/26556"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-01-20T13:26:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-19T08:52:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"333"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"41638"}}